<a class="definition-word" data-category="general-biology" id="ligand">Ligand</a> - A <a href="#molecule">molecule</a> (often small) that binds something (often much larger than the ligand) in a specific way. For example, an <a href="#inducer">inducer molecule</a> that binds a <a href="#transcription_factor_tf">transcription factor</a> is a ligand and caffeine is a ligand for a caffeine-specific <a href="#rna">RNA</a> <a href="#aptamer">aptamer</a>.